                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding notBefore="1475" notAfter="1650">
                                <p>Very finely decorated Safavid-era binding, possibly 17th century,
                                    with the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine">spine</locus> replaced
                                    in <date cert="high" from="1701" to="1800">18th-century</date>
                                    France, probably on behalf of former owner <persName
                                        ref="https://viaf.org/en/viaf/27161049"
                                        key="person_27161049" role="fmo seal">Chrétien-François de
                                        Lamoignon (1735–1789)</persName>, by a member of the
                                    Parisian Anguerrand family of binders to the French court,
                                    possibly <persName role="bnd" key="">Étienne II Anguerrand (fl.
                                        1750–1784)</persName> whose work remains largely
                                    unidentified.</p>
                                <p>Sewn at two stations, unsupported. Edges trimmed and chevron
                                    endbands twined at <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and
                                        <locus from="Tail" to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covered in full
                                    smooth dark brown goatskin <material>leather</material> over
                                        <material>pasteboards</material>, flush-cut with the edges
                                    and originally with a flap, now missing (Type II binding per
                                    Déroche). Interior doublures lined with the same leather.</p>
                                <decoNote>The exterior covers feature sunken gilt medallions,
                                    pendants and corner-pieces embossed with floral arabesques,
                                    while the interior doublures appear similar, with one or two
                                    leaves etc. picked out in blue. Replaced <locus from="Spine"
                                        to="Spine">spine</locus> bears a castle insignia in the tail
                                    panel and French title: <quote xml:lang="fr">AMOURS<lb/>DE
                                        MEHER<lb/> EN LANGUE<lb/>PERSIENNE</quote>. </decoNote>
                                <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                                        <height>230</height>
                                        <width>128</width>
                                        <depth>41</depth>
                                    </dimensions></p>
                                <condition>Handle binding with caution. The <locus
                                        from="Front_cover" to="Front_cover">right board</locus>
                                    detached, the <locus from="Back_cover" to="Back_cover">left
                                        board</locus> cracking. Tailband missing, sewing loose at
                                    the font, and very tight with opening to the gutter margins
                                    restricted. Boxed.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                        <sealDesc>
                            <summary>Folios <locus from="1Aa" to="1Aa">1a</locus>, <locus from="2b"
                                    to="2b">2b</locus>, <locus from="219a" to="219a">219a</locus>,
                                    <locus from="220b" to="220b">220b</locus> all bear impressions
